Don,
Back when I was a little more poorer than now and we had to go through
emissions testing for our year vehicles, I would take a stock engine off the
shelf and load it up in the bug/bus/truck and get it professionally tuned at
the VW garage and get the bug/bus/truck through emissions and get the tabs.
I would then pull the engine, put in the engine I wanted in there, and put
the tuned engine in one of the other cars for testing or back on the shelf.
Sounds unethical, I know, but it torques me off when we are forced to test
and tune, (at our great expense), newer cars to get our tabs, and older cars
can run around belching tons of pollutants without a second glance. Either
make it one way for everyone or not at all.

67 Single Cab, DP 1641cc 34PICT-3 (Thumper)
71 Trike 1776cc 32/36 Progressive
VolksAir 1585cc 28 PICT
Ray, Kent WA
Sometimes I feel like a mime in the dark
